Ola Arowolo Scholarship Programme

Terms and Conditions for Beneficiaries

By applying for and accepting this scholarship, you agree to the terms and conditions outlined below. These conditions govern your eligibility, responsibilities, continued participation, and access to funding throughout the programme.

1. Eligibility and Verification

1.1 You confirm that all information and documents submitted during the application process are accurate and authentic.
1.2 You must be an indigene or resident of Iba Town, Ojo, Lagos, or meet any additional eligibility criteria published by the programme.
1.3 You consent to verification of your identity, academic records, admission status, and any documents submitted.
1.4 Providing false or misleading information will result in immediate disqualification or withdrawal of support.

2. JAMB Stage Requirements

2.1 You must sit for the UTME in the year you apply.
2.2 If you fail to sit for the examination, your application will be closed.
2.3 Progression to the next stage requires a valid UTME result showing a pass.

3. Admission Stage Requirements

3.1 You must secure admission into a recognised Nigerian higher institution for the scholarship year.
3.2 You must submit evidence of admission, including JAMB CAPS confirmation and an official admission letter.
3.3 Admission documents must be genuine and verifiable.

4. N100,000 Admission Scholarship

4.1 You will receive N100,000 only after admission is fully confirmed.
4.2 Funds are applied strictly towards school fees.
4.3 If your school fees are less than N100,000, the balance may be held by the scholarship for future academic needs.
4.4 If your fees exceed N100,000, the full amount will be applied, and you are responsible for paying the remaining balance.
4.5 All payments must be made directly to the institution or through approved scholarship channels.

5. Performance Based Funding
A. Full Funding (100 percent fees)

5.1 You may receive full funding only if your first-year academic result shows a first-class CGPA.
5.2 You must maintain a first-class CGPA each session for continued full funding.
5.3 All academic results must be submitted within four weeks of release.
5.4 Any academic misconduct or falsification will lead to immediate withdrawal.

B. Partial Funding (Up to 50 percent fees)

5.5 You may receive up to 50 percent of your annual school fees if you maintain a CGPA of 4.0 or higher.
5.6 You must provide receipts and institutional documentation for verification.
5.7 Continued support is subject to performance review each academic year.

6. Academic Monitoring and Accountability

6.1 You must submit your academic results every semester or session as requested.
6.2 You must attend review meetings, mentoring sessions or follow-up engagements when scheduled.
6.3 A drop below 3.0 CGPA for two consecutive semesters may lead to suspension or termination of support.
6.4 You must uphold academic integrity, discipline, and good conduct at all times.

7. Communication and Updates

7.1 You must provide an active phone number and email address.
7.2 You are responsible for promptly updating the scholarship team if your contact details or academic status change.
7.3 Failure to respond to official communication may affect your eligibility.

8. Withdrawal, Suspension and Reversal of Funding

8.1 The scholarship may be suspended or withdrawn if any of the following occur:
• Falsification of results or documents
• Academic misconduct
• Failure to submit required documents
• Poor academic performance
• Behaviour that brings disrepute to the scholarship
8.2 Funds already disbursed may be recalled if awarded based on misleading or falsified information.
8.3 Suspended students may reapply for consideration after meeting improvement requirements.

9. Appeal Process

9.1 You may appeal any decision by submitting a written request with evidence within ten working days.
9.2 Appeals are reviewed on a case-by-case basis and decisions are final.

10. Use of Data

10.1 By participating, you consent to the use of your information for verification, communication, programme reporting and impact assessment.
10.2 Your details will not be shared with third parties except for verification or legal reasons.

11. Programme Changes

11.1 The scholarship may adjust its policies, funding structure, or terms at any time.
11.2 Changes will be communicated through official channels and will apply to both current and future beneficiaries.

12. Acceptance

By submitting your application, you confirm that you have read, understood and agreed to these Terms and Conditions. You accept that continued support depends on your academic performance, conduct, and compliance with all programme requirements.